      "text": [
        "هِ وَ لاَ أَعْلَمُ أَنَّهُ ذَكِيٌّ فَكَتَبَ «لاَ بَأْسَ بِهِ."
      ],
      "translations": {
        "en.bab-ul-qaim-publications": [
          "Hadith.793 - It was narrated from Ja'far ibn Muhammad ibn Yunus that his father wrote to Imam Abu Al-Hasan (as) asking about wearing fur or leather socks (khuff) and praying in them without knowing if they were from a properly slaughtered (halal) animal.\nHe (as) replied: \"There is no harm in it”."
        ]
      }
    },
